[[File:Rana_muscosa.jpg|thumb]][[卵|卵]]和[[蝌蚪|蝌蚪]]，因而会严重威胁[[两栖动物|两栖动物]]的生态]]
虹鳟对新环境（特别是[[温带|温带]]地区）的适应性优于鲑科大部分其它鱼类（比如[[褐鳟|褐鳟]]），可以忍耐夏季更高的水温，因此更容易在小型水体内存活，在被[[引入种|引进]]其原生栖息地以外的国家和地区后经常能成功建立可以自力更生的野生种群，以至于现在虹鳟鱼已经遍布世界上除了[[南极|南极]]以外的每个大[[洲|洲]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.iucn.org/places/medoffice/invasive_species/docs/invasive_species_booklet.pdf |title=IUCN: 100 of the World's Worst Invasive Alien Species |access-date=2007-11-23 |archive-date=2007-11-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071117151418/http://iucn.org/places/medoffice/invasive_species/docs/invasive_species_booklet.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://life.nthu.edu.tw/~labtcs/Salmon/crisis/mykiss_salmon.htm |title=櫻花鉤吻鮭的最大對手—虹鱒（Oncorhynchus mykiss） |access-date=2010-05-20 |archive-date=2021-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107100925/http://life.nthu.edu.tw/~labtcs/Salmon/crisis/mykiss_salmon.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Halverson |first=Anders |year=2010 |title=An Entirely Synthetic Fish: How Rainbow Trout Beguiled America and Overran the World |publisher=Yale University Press |location=New Haven, Connecticut |isbn=978-0-300-14088-0 |oclc=440281085}}</ref>。但将非原生物种如此广泛的增殖放流对各地的[[原生物种|原生物种]]会有严重的影响，而虹鳟这种食谱较广的肉食性动物会特别严重的威胁[[两栖动物|两栖动物]][[幼体|幼体]]和[[无脊椎动物|无脊椎动物]]的生态。因此，[[国际自然保护联盟|国际自然保护联盟]][[物种存续委员会|物种存续委员会]]的入侵物种专家小组（ISSG）已将虹鳟列为[[世界百大外来入侵种|世界百大外来入侵种]]之中。

美国内华达山脉的高山湖泊中原本没有自然生长的鱼，但有着丰富数量的[[黃腿山蛙|黃腿山蛙]]（''Rana muscosa''）。然而虹鳟的引入导致蛙类数量急剧下降直至[[濒危|濒危]]，以至于2001年后内华达山脉绝大多数湖泊的放流活动都停止，甚至开始了将虹鳟捕捞清除出湖泊的工程。

在[[新西兰|新西兰]]和[[南美|南美]]，虹鳟的放流对当地的[[休闲捕鱼|休闲垂钓]]和[[旅游业|旅游业]]有着良性的经济作用，同样成功被引入的还有[[褐鳟|褐鳟]]和其[[海鳟|海鳟]]亚种。但原生鱼群和其它野生动物却时常因为外来物种的到来而遭殃，比如新西兰的[[尖吻南茴魚|尖吻南茴魚]]（''Prototroctes oxyrhynchus''）就在1930年代因为引入鳟鱼带来的[[竞争_(生物学)|竞争]]和疾病而灭绝。

==经济价值==
===食用===
[[File:rainbow-trout-in-market.jpg|thumb]]一家[[水产品|水产]]市场出售的虹鳟]]
[[File:Pstruh_duhový_a_brambory.jpg|thumb]]
虹鳟在[[西方饮食|西方饮食]]中十分受欢迎，适合各种[[烹饪|烹饪]]方式食用，无论是野生还是养殖都属于上等的[[食用鱼|食用鱼]]。虹鳟的[[肉|肉]]质较嫩并带有味似[[坚果|坚果]]的微香<ref name=Harlow/>，而野生虹鳟则肉味要浓一些<ref name=Egan/>。虽然野生虹鳟更被[[美食家|美食家]]推崇<ref name=Wright/>，在[[美国|美国]][[餐厅|餐厅]]出售的虹鳟和“硬头鳟”其实通常都是[[水产养殖|人工养殖]]的<ref name=Wright>{{cite book|last=Wright|first=Leonard M.|title=Trout Maverick|year=1996|publisher=Lyons & Burford|location=New York|isbn=978-1-55821-476-7|page=19}}</ref>，因为养殖的虹鳟被认定为最安全的食用鱼之一并且富含[[维生素B|B组维生素]]，口感也很好<ref name=Cancila>{{cite web|last=Cancila|first=Katherine|title=The 5 Safest Fish to Eat – Salmon, Tilapia, Rainbow Trout and More|url=http://www.babble.com/best-recipes/safe-to-eat-fish-recipes-facts-5/|work=Babble|publisher=Disney|date=2010-09-16|access-date=2014-01-06|archive-date=2019-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109063212/https://www.babble.com/best-recipes/safe-to-eat-fish-recipes-facts-5/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并被[[蒙特雷湾水族馆|蒙特雷湾水族馆]]的《[[海鲜|海鲜]]观察》（Seafood Watch）名单列为适合人类食用的“最佳选择” 鱼种<ref name="Seafood Watch">{{cite web|last=O'Neill|first=Brendan|title=Seafood Watch Report: Farmed Rainbow Trout|url=http://www.seafoodwatch.org/cr/cr_seafoodwatch/content/media/MBA_SeafoodWatch_FarmedTroutReport.pdf|publisher=Monterey Bay Aquarium|access-date=2014-01-06|pages=2–6|date=2006-06-23|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107084804/http://www.seafoodwatch.org/cr/cr_seafoodwatch/content/media/MBA_SeafoodWatch_FarmedTroutReport.pdf|archive-date=2014-01-07}}</ref>。在[[蒙大拿州|蒙大拿州]]，因为野生虹鳟被法律定义为[[游钓鱼|游钓鱼]]<ref name=MCA101>{{cite web|title=§87-6-101, Montana Code Annotated|url=http://leg.mt.gov/bills/mca/87/6/87-6-101.htm|publisher=Montana Legislative Services|access-date=2014-01-06|year=2014|archive-date=2018-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180603182739/http://leg.mt.gov/bills/mca/87/6/87-6-101.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，销售野生捕捞的虹鳟是非法行为<ref name=MCA206>{{cite web|title=§87-6-206, Montana Code Annotated|url=http://leg.mt.gov/bills/mca/87/6/87-6-206.htm|publisher=Montana Legislative Services|access-date=2014-01-06|year=2014|archive-date=2018-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604000348/http://leg.mt.gov/bills/mca/87/6/87-6-206.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=MCA707>{{cite web|title=§87-6-707, Montana Code Annotated|url=http://leg.mt.gov/bills/mca/87/6/87-6-707.htm|publisher=Montana Legislative Services|access-date=2014-01-06|year=2014|archive-date=2020-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001141644/https://leg.mt.gov/bills/mca/87/6/87-6-707.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，因此只能购买到养殖的虹鳟。

虹鳟的肉色和口感取决于其食谱和新鲜度。养殖的鳟鱼和一些野生鳟（特别是[[洄游|洄游]]的硬头鳟）因为饮食中有大量的[[虾红素|虾红素]]所以肉色发红或发橙色。因为野生硬头鳟在许多栖息地的数量在减少，养殖的虹鳟被[[美国|美国]]水产商视为优先考虑的选项<ref name=Monterey/>，通常会将虾红素摄入量高（包括以[[食用色素|色素]]形式[[添加剂|添加]]在[[饲料|饲料]]中的）因而肉色更粉的养殖鱼贴上“硬头鳟”的标签销售<ref name=Harlow>{{cite web |title=Dependable, Delectable Rainbow Trout |author=Harlow, Jay |publisher=Sally's Place |url=http://www.sallybernstein.com/food/columns/harlow/rainbow_trout.htm |access-date=2013-11-28 |archive-date=2022-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129063641/https://sallybernstein.com/food/columns/harlow/rainbow_trout.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在[[智利|智利]]和[[挪威|挪威]]，用海水养殖笼产出的虹鳟通常用“硬头鳟”的名义销售<ref name="Seafood Watch"/>。在[[澳洲|澳洲]][[塔斯马尼亚|塔斯马尼亚]]引进养殖的海栖虹鳟则通常是淡水虹鳟和硬头鳟的[[杂交种|杂交种]]，商业上俗称“洋鳟”（ocean trout）<ref name="Tasmania"/>。

鳟鱼和[[鲑鱼|鲑鱼]]一样可以在清洗后就马上烹饪，不需要[[鱼鳞|去鳞]]、[[剥皮|剥皮]]或[[菲力|切柳]]<ref name=Wright/>。如果带皮烹煮的话往往更有利于肉质保持完整<ref name=Harlow/>。在[[欧洲|欧洲]]销售的虹鳟通常整条烹饪，但[[美国人|美国人]]的习惯则是切掉鱼头后剔骨切柳。欧美人在食用虹鳟时通常会配饮[[白葡萄酒|白葡萄酒]]，比如[[霞多丽|霞多丽]]或[[白苏维浓|长相思]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://winefolly.com/tutorial/wine-with-fish-pairing-guide/ |title=Pairing Wine with Fish |publisher=Wine Folly |access-date=2014-02-15 |date=May 20, 2013 |archive-date=2022-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129070542/https://winefolly.com/tutorial/wine-with-fish-pairing-guide/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

虹鳟能寄生23种原生生物寄生虫<ref>Lom J, Dykova I. Protozoan parasites of fishes. Developments in aquaculture and fisheries science, 26. 1992. Elsevier, Amsterdam, p 1-315</ref>和至少169种后生生物寄生虫<ref>Buchmann K, et al. A checklist of metazoan parasites from rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss). Acta Vet Scand. 1995;36(3):299-318.</ref>。养殖的虹鳟同样容易被寄生虫感染，例如对[[丹麦|丹麦]]的虹鳟淡水养殖场的抽查，发现了10种后生生物寄生虫和10种原生生物寄生虫<ref>Buchmann K, et al. Parasite infections in Danish trout farms. Acta Vet Scand. 1995;36(3):283-98.</ref>。[[阿根廷|阿根廷]]科学家报道，抽查了阿根廷南部一个湖里的114条虹鳟，找到了两种[[廣節裂頭絛蟲|廣節裂頭絛蟲]]，感染率分别是57.8%和28.0%<ref>Revenga JE. Diphyllobothrium dendriticum and Diphyllobothrium latum in fishes from southern Argentina: association, abundance, distribution, pathological effects, and risk of human infection. J Parasitol. 1993 Jun;79(3):379-83.</ref>。智利科学家报道，他们抽查了智利引进的虹鳟，阔节裂头绦虫感染率高达71%，虹鳟肉中阔节裂头绦虫感染率高达62%<ref>Torres P, et al. Prevalence, intensity, and abundance of infection and pathogenesis caused by diphyllobothriosis in vulnerable, native fish and introduced trout in Lake Panguipulli, Chile. J Wildl Dis. 2012 Oct;48(4):937-50.</ref>。对从10个[[智利|智利]]虹鳟养殖场逃逸的虹鳟抽查结果，阔节裂头绦虫感染率是9.2%，但是有的地方感染率高达50.9%<ref>Rozas M, et al. First molecular identification of Diphyllobothrium dendriticum plerocercoids from feral rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss) in Chile. J Parasitol. 2012 Dec;98(6):1220-6.</ref>。智利科学家还抽查了智利南部8个养殖场的虹鳟，发现了阔节裂头绦虫。鱼肉里的寄生虫是可以经过冷冻杀死的。[[美国食品药品监督管理局|美国食品药品监督管理局]]的要求是生鱼肉在{{convert|-20|C|F|lk=on}}冷冻7天，或在{{convert|-35|C|F}}冷冻15小时，才能食用。

====“三文鱼”争议====
{{main|真假「三文魚」之争}}
[[File:鮭魚生魚片.jpg|thumb]]与鲑鱼生鱼片的外表几乎一模一样]]
由於虹鱒的肉質和顏色與同科的[[大西洋鲑|大西洋鲑]]非常相近，而價格較低，因此有些[[壽司|壽司]][[日本料理|料理店]]會以虹鱒肉當作鮭魚肉出售。而野生和开放圈养的[[淡水|淡水]]虹鱒十分容易被[[寄生蟲|寄生蟲]]感染，理論上需要烹煮消毒過才可使用，不可以當作[[刺身|刺身]]生吃<ref>[http://news.memehk.com/posts/19896 《生食鮭魚》團體發佈淡水虹鱒歸類鮭魚 網民：「國內的鮭魚再見！」] {{Wayback|url=http://news.memehk.com/posts/19896 |date=20210415115643 }}  Memehk 2018年8月13日</ref>。

据2018年5月的报道，[[中國大陸|中國大陸]]市面上三分之一的[[三文魚|三文魚]]由[[青海省|青海省]]供應，事後被揭發青海的湖泊養殖場內是淡水虹鱒，可能含有大量寄生蟲不適合生食。到2018年8月10日，中國水產流通與加工協會正式發布《生食鮭魚》團體標準，將虹鱒直接定性為三文鱼品种之一<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-45178638 |title=Rainbow trout can now be called salmon in China |work=BBC News |date=August 14, 2018 |accessdate=2022-01-29 |archive-date=2018-09-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180901100050/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-45178638 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/china-rainbow-trout-salmon-fish-sales-counterfeit-a8491361.html |title=China rules rainbow trout can now be sold as salmon, in attempt to reduce counterfeit fish sales |work=The Independent |date=August 14, 2018 |accessdate=2022-01-29 |archive-date=2018-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818103509/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/china-rainbow-trout-salmon-fish-sales-counterfeit-a8491361.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/aug/14/china-rainbow-trout-and-salmon-the-same-thing |title=Very fishy: China rules rainbow trout can be sold as salmon |work=The Guardian |date=August 14, 2018 |accessdate=2022-01-29 |archive-date=2018-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180909152000/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/aug/14/china-rainbow-trout-and-salmon-the-same-thing |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此舉被认为涉嫌允许用虹鳟充当进口鮭魚侵犯消费者的[[知情权|知情权]]因而引发[[舆论|舆论]]争议，认为在[[食品卫生|食品卫生]]監管缺失的情况下只可能助长食用混乱<ref>[http://finance.sina.com.cn/chanjing/cyxw/2018-08-13/doc-ihhqtawy2261286.shtml 虹鳟归入鮭魚？团体标准制定更需吸纳民意] {{Wayback|url=http://finance.sina.com.cn/chanjing/cyxw/2018-08-13/doc-ihhqtawy2261286.shtml |date=20210415115649 }} 新浪财经-自媒体综合 2018年8月13日</ref>。[[上海海洋大学|上海海洋大學]]教授陳舜勝稱，生食虹鱒危害健康，《團體標準》提出的消滅寄生蟲的方法{{哪个|reason=什么方法？}}僅適用於海水魚<ref>[https://china.hket.com/article/2136318/%E5%85%A7%E5%9C%B0%E6%B0%B4%E7%94%A2%E5%9C%98%E9%AB%94%E6%A8%99%E6%BA%96%EF%BC%9A%E8%99%B9%E9%B1%92%E6%AD%B8%E5%85%A5%E4%B8%89%E6%96%87%E9%AD%9A%20%E5%B0%88%E5%AE%B6%E7%A8%B1%E7%94%9F%E9%A3%9F%E6%81%90%E5%8D%B1%E5%8F 中國內地水產團體標準：虹鱒歸入鮭魚 專家稱生食恐危及健康]  香港經濟日報 2018-08-13 </ref>。

===游钓===
[[File:Fly_caught_rainbow_trout_Madison_River_YNP.JPG|thumb]]群体中极受欢迎的游钓鱼]]
虹鳟和硬头鳟是[[垂钓|垂钓]]（特别是[[飞蝇钓|飞蝇钓]]）爱好者中非常受欢迎的[[游钓鱼|游钓鱼]]，有多种使用[[拟饵|假饵]]的[[拟钓|拟钓]]手法，也可以用活的或死的天然[[鱼饵|鱼饵]]诱钓。因为虹鳟上钩后会用力跳跃和挣扎（所谓的“洗鳃”），许多垂钓者将其评价为反抗最激烈的鳟鱼<ref>{{cite book |last=Waterman |first=Charles F. |title=The Fisherman's World |publisher=Random House |location=New York |year=1971 |page=[https://archive.org/details/fishermansworld00wate/page/57 57] |isbn=978-0-394-41099-9 |oclc=319916607 |url=https://archive.org/details/fishermansworld00wate/page/57 }}</ref>。虹鳟是[[北美洲|北美洲]]五种顶级游钓鱼之一，并且是[[落基山脉|落基山脉]]以西最重要的游钓鱼<ref name=fwsRainbow/>。 国际钓鱼运动协会（International Game Fish Association，简称IGFA）所承认的世界纪录是2009年9月5日在[[加拿大|加拿大]][[萨斯喀彻温省|萨斯喀彻温省]][[迪芬贝克湖|迪芬贝克湖]]捕捉到的一条重{{convert|48|lb|kg|lk=on}}的虹鳟，是条从孵化场逃脱的[[基因改造|基因改造]]过的种鱼<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2009/09/biotechfishing/|title=48-Pound Trout: World Record or Genetic Cheat?|work=Wired|author=Keim, Brandon|date=2009-09-15|access-date=2013-11-29|archive-date=2021-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720125427/https://www.wired.com/2009/09/biotechfishing/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[普吉特海湾|普吉特海湾]]、[[华盛顿州|华盛顿]]沿岸和[[哥伦比亚河|哥伦比亚河]]有许多用来捕捉硬头鳟的[[北美原住民|部落]]商业[[渔场|渔场]]，但这些渔场引发了有关[[过度捕捞|过度捕捞]]的争议<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://scholarship.law.umt.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1255&context=plrlr |title=Under the Guise of 'Treaty Rights:' The Nez Perce Tribe of Idaho, Steelhead, and Gillnetting |journal=Public Land and Resources Law Review |volume=29 |author=Stellmon, Josh |year=2008 |access-date=2014-01-05 |archive-date=2017-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525110832/http://scholarship.law.umt.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1255&context=plrlr |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

因为在钓鱼爱好者中的受欢迎程度以及其对孵化场和新环境的强大[[适应|适应]]能力，虹鳟被[[引入种|引进]]到了世界各地的水域，也因而在一些地区与[[原生物种|原生物种]][[竞争_(生物学)|竞争]]造成了环境和生态问题<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.issg.org/database/species/search.asp?st=100ss |title=100 of the World's Worst Invasive Alien Species |publisher=Invasive Species Specialist Group (ISSG) of the IUCN Species Survival Commission |access-date=2013-11-28 |archive-date=2015-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150429045453/http://www.issg.org/database/species/search.asp?st=100ss |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而一些之前缺鱼的[[水体|水体]]在引入虹鳟[[增殖放流|增殖放流]]后变成了世界级的高级渔场，比如[[五大湖|五大湖]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dec.ny.gov/outdoor/58841.html |title=Fishing New York's Great Lakes |publisher=New York State Department of Environmental Conservation |access-date=2013-11-28 |archive-date=2021-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210609153701/https://www.dec.ny.gov/outdoor/58841.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>和[[黄石国家公园|黄石国家公园]]中的火洞河（Firehole River）<ref name="Brooks 1979 56–59">{{cite book |last=Brooks |first=Charles E. |title=The Living River: A Fisherman's Intimate Profile of the Madison River Watershed—Its History, Ecology, Lore and Angling Opportunities |url=https://archive.org/details/petermillersskia0000mill |publisher=Nick Lyons Books |location=Garden City, New Jersey |pages=[https://archive.org/details/petermillersskia0000mill/page/56 56]–59 |year=1979 |isbn=978-0-385-15655-4 |oclc=5751574}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_nweqC_fUcwC |title=The Yellowstone Fly-Fishing Guide |author4=Matthews, Craig and Molinero, Clayton |publisher=The Globe Pequot Press |location=Guilford, CT |isbn=978-1-55821-545-0 |page=11 |quote=In 1994 Yellowstone Park official introduced a fee permit policy to help pay the increased cost of protecting and enhancing this world-class fishery.|year=1997}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L8gbWk-TBJYC&pg=RA1-PT254 |author=Santella, Chris |title=Fifty Places to Fly Fish Before You Die: Fly Fishing Experts Share The World's Greatest Destinations |isbn=978-1-58479-356-4 |chapter=Brown and Rainbow trout on the Madison River |publisher=Harry M. Abrams Inc |year=2004 |quote=... thanks to the Firehole's geothermal activity, the river bottom undulates with plant life. Few fish are caught here and tourists continue on to the West Yellowstone park exit, thinking that it's too bad there are no fish in that pretty river that skirts the road. Little do they know that they have been following one of the most fabled trout streams in the world! |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/fiftyplacestofly00sant }}</ref><!-- Many sources, both government and commercial have referred to these fisheries as "world class" in some form or another -->。

